<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<taxonomicName LSID="7FEFCA6A-C53D-5FEE-AF4B-7F011B9C410F" authority="Leach, 1817" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1817" class="Insecta" family="Cimbicidae" genus="Abia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Abia brevicornis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicornis" status="nom. rev.">Abia brevicornis Leach, 1817</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="0" pageNumber="151">nom. rev.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="151" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Liston &amp; Mutanen &amp; Heidemaa &amp; Blank &amp; Kiljunen &amp; Taeger &amp; Viitasaari &amp; Vikberg &amp; Wutke &amp; Prous" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Cimbicidae" genus="Abia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Abia brevicornis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicornis" status="nom. rev.">Abia brevicornis</taxonomicName>
Leach, 1817: 114. Sex not stated [but probably female, because conspicuous dark dorsal patches on abdomen are not mentioned]. Syntypes (assumed). Type locality: not stated. Type material probably lost or destroyed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Liston &amp; Mutanen &amp; Heidemaa &amp; Blank &amp; Kiljunen &amp; Taeger &amp; Viitasaari &amp; Vikberg &amp; Wutke &amp; Prous" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Cimbicidae" genus="Cimbex" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cimbex splendida" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="splendida" status="nom. rev.">Cimbex splendida</taxonomicName>
Klug, 1820 [incorrect original spelling]: 98-99. ♀, ♂. Syntypes. Type locality: Germany; rare in this area [around Berlin]. Syntype ♂ [examined]: 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“GBIF-GISHym2903”">&quot;GBIF-GISHym2903&quot;</normalizedToken>
, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“13567”">&quot;13567&quot;</normalizedToken>
, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Germania”">&quot;Germania&quot;</normalizedToken>
, &quot;nitens L. Soldanski det.&quot;. ZMHB.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Liston &amp; Mutanen &amp; Heidemaa &amp; Blank &amp; Kiljunen &amp; Taeger &amp; Viitasaari &amp; Vikberg &amp; Wutke &amp; Prous" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Cimbicidae" genus="Abia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Abia rossica" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rossica" status="nom. rev.">Abia rossica</taxonomicName>
Semenov, 1896: 159, 167-168. ♀. Holotype [not examined]. Type locality: Ukraine, Kamjanez-Podilskyj.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Liston &amp; Mutanen &amp; Heidemaa &amp; Blank &amp; Kiljunen &amp; Taeger &amp; Viitasaari &amp; Vikberg &amp; Wutke &amp; Prous" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Cimbicidae" genus="Abia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Abia nitens" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitens" status="nom. rev.">Abia nitens</taxonomicName>
auct. nec Linnaeus. Misidentification of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Liston &amp; Mutanen &amp; Heidemaa &amp; Blank &amp; Kiljunen &amp; Taeger &amp; Viitasaari &amp; Vikberg &amp; Wutke &amp; Prous" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Cimbicidae" genus="Tenthredo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tenthredo nitens" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitens" status="nom. rev.">Tenthredo nitens</taxonomicName>
by, for example: 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.10348" author="de Dalla Torre, CG" journalOrPublisher="Berling, Lund" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" refId="B37" refString="de Dalla Torre, CG, 1894. Catalogus Hymenopterorum hucusque descriptorum systematicus et synonymicus. Vol. 1: Tenthredinidae incl. Uroceridae (Phyllophaga &amp; Xylophaga). Guilelmus Engelmann, Lipsiae, [[6] pp.+ pp. I-VIII +] 1-459. https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.10348" title="Catalogus Hymenopterorum hucusque descriptorum systematicus et synonymicus. Vol. 1: Tenthredinidae incl. Uroceridae (Phyllophaga &amp; Xylophaga). Guilelmus Engelmann, Lipsiae, [[ 6] pp. + pp. I-VIII +] 1 - 459." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.10348" year="1894">de Dalla Torre (1894)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Konow, FW" journalOrPublisher="Genera Insectorum" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="1 - 176" refId="B99" refString="Konow, FW, 1905b. Hymenoptera. Fam. Tenthredinidae. Genera Insectorum 29: 1 - 176" title="Hymenoptera. Fam. Tenthredinidae." volume="29" year="1905 b">Konow (1905b)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Taeger, A" editor="Taeger, A" journalOrPublisher="Kommentierte Bestandsaufnahme. Goecke and Evers, Keltern" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="193 - 205" refId="B171" refString="Taeger, A, 1998. Bestimmungsschluessel der Keulhornblattwespen Deutschlands (Hymenoptera: Cimbicidae). In: Taeger, A, Blank, SM, Eds., Pflanzenwespen Deutschlands (Hymenoptera, Symphyta). Kommentierte Bestandsaufnahme. Goecke and Evers, Keltern: 193 - 205" title="Bestimmungsschluessel der Keulhornblattwespen Deutschlands (Hymenoptera: Cimbicidae)." volumeTitle="Pflanzenwespen Deutschlands (Hymenoptera, Symphyta)." year="1998">Taeger (1998)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Liston, AD" editor="Blank, SM" journalOrPublisher="Goecke and Evers, Keltern" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="129 - 138" refId="B117" refString="Liston, AD, Spaeth, J, 2006. On the Biology of Abia nitens (Linne, 1758): a Thermophile Sawfly with a Diurnal Larval Feeding-Pattern (Hymenoptera: Symphyta: Cimbicidae). In: Blank, SM, Schmidt, S, Taeger, A, Eds., Recent Sawfly Research: Synthesis and Prospects. Goecke and Evers, Keltern: 129 - 138" title="On the Biology of Abia nitens (Linne, 1758): a Thermophile Sawfly with a Diurnal Larval Feeding-Pattern (Hymenoptera: Symphyta: Cimbicidae)." volumeTitle="Recent Sawfly Research: Synthesis and Prospects." year="2006">
Liston and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Späth">Spaeth</normalizedToken>
(2006)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
