<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="151" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2580.1.1" author="Taeger, A" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="1 - 1064" refId="B173" refString="Taeger, A, Blank, SM, Liston, AD, 2010. World Catalog of Symphyta (Hymenoptera). Zootaxa 2580 (1): 1 - 1064, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2580.1.1" title="World Catalog of Symphyta (Hymenoptera)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2580.1.1" volume="2580" year="2010">Taeger et al. (2010)</bibRefCitation>
also listed 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Cimbicidae" genus="Abia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Abia nitens subsp. var. var. vernetensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="nitens" subSpecies="var." variety="vernetensis">Abia nitens var. vernetensis</taxonomicName>
Pic, 1928 (type locality: France, Allier) as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Liston &amp; Mutanen &amp; Heidemaa &amp; Blank &amp; Kiljunen &amp; Taeger &amp; Viitasaari &amp; Vikberg &amp; Wutke &amp; Prous" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Cimbicidae" genus="Abia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Abia nitens" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Abia nitens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
auct. However, no type specimen has been examined subsequent to its description, as far as we are aware. Pic wrote [translated from French] &quot;differs from the typical form in the black-marked base of the posterior femora&quot;. This suggests that it possibly does not belong to 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. brevicornis" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="brevicornis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">A. brevicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
